    "objective": "“to estimate valproic acid (VPA) clearance values for adult patients with epilepsy, using serum concentrations gathered during their routine clinical care.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: DDVPA, SEX, WT, Comedication (CBZ, PHT, PHB) Included: WT, DDVPA, CBZ, PHT, PHB",
    "observations": "Inter-individual plus residual variability’s, remaining in the final model, render these dosage predictions imprecise. Cpred vs Cobs plot shows moderate distribution of points along the unit line., slight over prediction of the final model is seen. Results show that VPA clearance increased linearly with TBW, but increases nonlinearly with increasing VPA daily dose. Concomitant administration of CBZ, PHT and PB led to a significant increase in VPA clearance.",
